{
  "monologue": "I can't share my private chain-of-thought, but here is a concise rationale: given your high stress sensitivity and strong need for structure, reinforcing the ultra-simple anchor and adding a brief post-log reflection supports consistent habit formation without adding cognitive load, helping you edge toward the target behavior level.",
  "utterance": "You're doing well. Tonight, continue with the ultra-simple anchor: 60-second pause, three slow breaths, a glass of water, and log your hunger. If you are still hungry after the pause, choose the smallest pre-planned option and log it. After you log, spend a moment noting one thing that helped you pause (for example your breath, the water, or your environment) and one small adjustment you could try tomorrow. Keeping it straightforward and honest supports your BED goals.",
  "endkey": false
}
